                            <comment id="12622398" author="ryantxu" created="Thu, 14 Aug 2008 00:57:26 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Here is a patch (with loads of help from Henri) that gets rid of the &quot;singlecore&quot; concept.  Single core is now a CoreContainer with one Core registered to the name &quot;&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The one functional change in this patch is that it adds a &quot;managementPath&quot; in the &amp;lt;solr/cores&amp;gt; xml configuration.  This gives a way to access other cores when a core is registered to &quot;&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12622416" author="ryantxu" created="Thu, 14 Aug 2008 02:47:52 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;In the interest of getting this reviewed/tested ASAP, I will go ahead and commit this now...  as always, we can revert if anything is amiss.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12622633" author="ryantxu" created="Thu, 14 Aug 2008 19:37:03 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Here is a patch that refactors the remaining &quot;MultiCore&quot; references.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The key classes it renames are:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;MultiCoreRequest -&amp;gt; CoreAdminRequest&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;MultiCoreResponse -&amp;gt; CoreAdminResponse&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;MultiCoreParams -&amp;gt; CoreAdminParams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;I also added:&lt;br/&gt;
 &lt;a href=&quot;http://wiki.apache.org/solr/CoreAdmin&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://wiki.apache.org/solr/CoreAdmin&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;a page that should replace (and get directed from) MultiCore&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
